  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Living with History, 1914-1964\" published by Leuven University Press in 2021, showcases an academic exploration of historical contexts, although it currently has not gained significant traction across various scholarly and public platforms.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Despite its publication in 2021, \"Living with History, 1914-1964\" has yet to establish a measurable footprint in citations or community discourse on platforms such as Wikipedia or Reddit. This lack of mentions suggests that while the work is academically oriented, it has not resonated broadly in public discussions or engaged wider audiences.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The book's inferred roles indicate a strong commercial linkage, with indications of availability on platforms like Amazon and Goodreads, which may facilitate accessibility to a wider readership. However, the evidence shows that engagement beyond initial availability remains low, with zero events or discussions recorded across significant community platforms.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The work demonstrates some relevance to sustainability and policy, as evidenced by its association with a single Sustainable Development Goal (SDG), reflecting its potential applicability to contemporary issues. However, with a scholarly uptake strength rating of 0.45, the current citation count suggests that it has not yet reached an influential status within the academic community.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">In summary, while \"Living with History, 1914-1964\" stands as a scholarly output worthy of examination, it has not yet forged a path into broader academic or public acknowledgment, highlighting an opportunity for further engagement and discussion within its historical themes.</p>",
